      "span_text": "The ecdysone-inducible system, based on the insect hormone ecdysone analog ponasterone A, was employed in alternative to the tetracycline-regulated technology. A ponasterone A-responsive 293T-based cell line was generated in which the expression of gag, pol, rev and VSV-g genes was placed under control of an inducible ecdysone promoter."
